            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> It seems that this has been fixed in [krischik/vim-ada@32e5b9e](https://github.com/krischik/vim-ada/commit/32e5b9edc56856fa400575691ade4486215f7847) but the fix still hasn't been add to Vim runtime.\n\nYes, an update to the newest version might be helpful: https://github.com/krischik/vim-ada. However, I'm **not** a neovim runtime maintainer as I use GVim. I have absolutely no idea how to update the runtime. Last time I just send a ZIP to Bram and he did the rest.\n\nI did make the bundle Deim, Plug, etc compatible so it can be imported via you favourite plugin manager which might be the easier option. Which is in fact what I do and makes more sense for a large bundle.\n\nAlso note that this is a bundle consisting of a dozen scripts. You can't just replace one part. You have to replace it all.\n",
